cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.COMM, cs.CR, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses the performance of TCP over high BDP networks, which falls under the scope of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper compares the performance of single-based and parallel TCP, which involves distributed and parallel computing. 
3. cs.COMM (Computer Communication Networks) - The paper discusses the impact of parallelism on throughput and fairness in heterogeneous networks, which falls under the scope of computer communication networks. 
4. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - Although the paper does not directly discuss cryptography and security, it may indirectly relate to security issues in network communication. 
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper involves the study of system performance and control in network communication.
